  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the sentencing guidelines for this amount typically favor a period of incarceration that balances punishment with the potential for rehabilitation. The outburst from the spectator is irrelevant to the legal merits of the case and has been disregarded. A sentence of 8 months is sufficient to uphold the law and deter future conduct without being excessive for a first-time offense of this nature.",
